{In the following example, the GM Zaja found an amazing fortress and saved
this hard endgame with ease. White, a pawn ahead, is ready to move his king to
the queenside while the Black king is tied up to restrain the passer.} 58... b4
$1 59. axb4 axb4 60. Bd4 Na5 ({Or} 60... Nd2) 61. Ke4 Nb3 $1 62. Kd5 Na1 $1 63.
Kc4 b3 {[#] The passed pawn is under control while the black pawn is safe as
the bishop cannot attack its guard.} 1/2-1/2

