{In this game, White didn't recognize Black's threat.} 1. Qxa3 $2 {Without the
"e2" and "a3" pawns Black can set up a fortress.} ({White could win after the
correct} 1. Qa8+ $1 Kg7 2. e4 Rg6+ 3. Kf4 {, keeping both pawns alive}) 1...
Rxe2 2. Qc3 ({After} 2. Qb3 Re6 $1 {draws easily}) 2... Re6 $1 {Now Black's
defence is straightforward. Just move the rook from "g6 to "e6". The only
thing which Black should look for is not to enter a lost pawn endgame.} 3. Kf5
({Or} 3. Qd3 Kg7 $11 (3... Rg6+ $4 4. Qxg6+ $1 fxg6 5. Kxg6 $18 {.})) 3... Kh7
4. Qd4 Rg6 5. Qd8 Kg7 6. g4 Rh6 7. g5 Rg6 {White tried for a few more moves,
but it is already evident that he can't make any progress.} *

