{Earlier Andersson realized the same defensive idea in the following position.
} 28... h6 $1 {[%cal Gg8h7,Gf8h8] If Black doesn't make this move, White can
develop his attack by means of g4-g5 or h4-h5. After ... Kh7 followed by ...
Rh8, White cannot easily open the kingside due to the vulnerability of his own
king.} 29. Rf2 ({Another point behind 28...h6 is that} 29. h5 {will be met by}
g5 {, thus closing the kingside.}) 29... Kh7 $5 30. Rdf1 Rh8 $5 31. Bh3 Kg8 32.
fxg6 {Opens the f-file for the rooks, but gives the kingside space advantage
away.} ({After} 32. g5 {was possible} hxg5 33. Bxg5 Bh6 $132 {[%csl Bh4]} 34.
Bxh6 Rxh6 {[%csl Rh1][%cal Gg8g7,Gd8h8] Black is planning to proceed with ...
Kg7 followed by ...Qh8. White's king is more vulnerable now.}) 32... fxg6 33.
Bb2 Be6 34. h5 ({After} 34. g5 $6 Bxh3 35. Qxh3 Qc8 36. Qxc8+ Rxc8 37. Bxe5
Bxe5 $15 {Black is better since White's kingside is hanging.}) 34... Qd7 35.
hxg6 Nxg6 36. Bxg7 Kxg7 37. Kg1 Rbf8 38. Rxf8 $2 {Now, the g4-pawn becomes
vulnerable.} ({Better would have been} 38. Rf5 {keeping the balance.}) 38...
Rxf8 39. Rxf8 Kxf8 40. Qe3 Kg7 41. d4 Bxg4 42. Bg2 cxd4 43. Qxd4+ Kh7 44. Qb6
$2 {Loses immediately.} (44. e5 Nxe5 45. c5 $17) 44... Bh3 45. Bf3 Ne5 46. Be2
Bg4 47. Bf1 Bf3 {0-1 White resigns.} 0-1

[Event "EU-Cup 24th"]
