{[#]} 22... Kg8 $1 {By removing the king from opposition with Qh4 Black
prepares for White`s action.} 23. f4 (23. Na4 Re5 $1 24. f4 Ra5 25. Nac3 (25.
e5 $6 Qb7 $1) {leads to the game after} 25... h6 $1 26. Qxh6 Rxg5 $3) ({
perhaps the best was} 23. b4 $5 Rxc4 24. Bd3 Rxb4 25. Bxa6 {[%cal Ga6b5] with
compensation for the pawn.}) 23... h6 $1 24. Qxh6 (24. Bxh6 $4 Rh5 $19) (24.
Bxf6 Nxf6 $132) 24... Rxg5 $3 25. Qxg5 (25. fxg5 $4 Nh5 {[%csl Rh6][%cal Ge7f8]
}) 25... Nxe4 26. Qh6 Nf2+ 27. Kg1 Bf8 $5 {Avoiding possible sacrifice on g6.}
({Black had no time to calculate the variation} 27... Nxd1 28. Bxg6 $2 Nf8 $1)
28. Qh4 $6 (28. Qg5 Nxd1 29. Rxd1 Qc8 30. Be4 Bxe4 31. Nxe4 Qc6 $132) 28...
Nxd1 29. Rxd1 b5 $1 {In result, Black seizes the initiative.} 30. cxb5 axb5 31.
Ne4 $2 {A blunder in mutual time-trouble.} Bxe4 32. Bxe4 Qa7+ 33. Kh1 Qxa2 34.
Nd4 d5 35. Bb1 Qb2 36. Qg3 Bg7 37. Nxb5 Rb8 38. Bd3 Qxb3 39. Rb1 Qa4 40. Qf2 d4
41. Qf1 Nc5 42. Ra1 Qb4 43. Rb1 Qd2 44. Bc4 (44. Rd1 Qe3 $19) 44... d3 $1 45.
g3 Qc2 (45... Qc2 46. Rc1 Bb2 $1 47. Rxc2 dxc2 $19) 0-1

