{[#] Active or passive defence against Nxf2 threat?} 37. h3 {Active is better!}
({Passive defense is risky:} 37. Rcc1 Nxh2 (37... Rg5 38. Bd7 Nxh2 39. Rg1) 38.
Kxh2 Rg5 39. Be8 Rxe8 40. Kh3 Reg8 41. Kh4 Rg2 42. Rh1 Rxf2) (37. Rc2 Rg5 38.
Bd7 Nxh2) 37... Rg5 {[#]} (37... Ne3 $5 {was an interesting option, but Black
may also risk something with a piece sacrifice.} 38. fxe3 Rg3 (38... fxe3 39.
Rc6 $1 Rg3 40. Rxh6+ Kg7 41. Rh4 e2 42. Bxe2 fxe2 43. Re1 $11) 39. Kh2 Rg2+ 40.
Kh1 fxe3 (40... R8g3 41. Rc8+ Kg7 42. Rc7+ Kf6 43. Rc6+ Kg5 44. h4+ $1 (44.
exf4+ Kh5 $1 45. Rxf3 Rg1+ 46. Kh2 R3g2#) 44... Kh5 45. Rxf3 Rg1+ 46. Kh2 R3g2+
47. Kh3 Rg4 48. Kh2 $11) 41. Rcc1 $1 e2 42. Bxe2 fxe2 43. Rfe1 Rf2 44. Rg1 $1
Rgf8 45. d6 $1 Rf1 46. d7 $11) 38. Bd7 $1 {Active defense saves the day} ({
Passive does not work here} 38. Rc3 Rh5 39. Rxf3 Ne5 40. Ra3 (40. Rb3 f3) 40...
f3 $1 $19) 38... Rh5 (38... Ne3 39. Rb1 (39. fxe3 fxe3 $19 {[%csl Rd7]}) 39...
Rg2 40. fxe3 fxe3 41. Bg4 e2 42. Rcc1 h5 43. Bxh5 R2g3 44. Kh2 Rg2+ $11) (38...
Ne5 39. Be6) 39. Rc8 $1 $11 {The point. White king is not in the mating net
any more.} (39. Bxg4 $2 Rxg4 40. Rc8+ Kg7 41. Rc7+ Kf6 42. Rc6+ Kf5 $19) 39...
Rxh3+ 40. Kg1 Rh5 (40... Rh2 41. Rxg8+ Kxg8 42. Bxg4 Rg2+ 43. Kh1 Rxg4 44. d6
Kf7 45. Re1 Rg6 46. d7 Rd6 47. Re4 Rxd7 48. Rxf4+ Ke6 49. Rxf3 $11) 41. d6 Rxc8
42. Bxc8 Rg5 43. Bxg4 Rxg4+ 44. Kh2 Rh4+ 45. Kg1 Rg4+ 46. Kh2 1/2-1/2

