{[#] White position is objectively losing as his king is weak and Black has
passed pawns. He made things more difficult for Black with active defence :} 
28. Bg2 Ra5 29. Be4 Rc5 30. c4 $5 {This active move weakens the king
irreparably, but makes the position more dynamic and tricky.} ({Passive
defence like} 30. R3d2 {is bound to fail.} Qa5 31. Re2 Qxe1 32. Rdxe1 g3 $19)
30... Bb7 31. Bxb7 Qxb7 32. h5 Qf7 33. b4 $1 {The best choice in a losing
position, posing concrete practical problems to Black, who was also in a time
scramble.} (33. Qb4 Rc8 34. Qxa3 Rf1 35. Qc1 Qf5 $19) 33... Rf2 $4 $138 {
White blunders under sudden pressure.} (33... Rxc4 {is the most obvious move,
but it is not clear if Black is winning after} 34. Qxe5 Rxb4+ 35. Ka1) (33...
Rc8 $1 {is the right move, but not easy to find.} 34. Rxa3 (34. Qxe5 Qxc4 $1
$19) 34... Qxc4 35. Rc1 Qxc1+ 36. Qxc1 Rxc1+ 37. Kxc1 e4 $19) 34. bxc5 {
Black missed something as White can easily parry all threats.} Rb2+ (34... Qb7+
35. Rb3 Rb2+ 36. Ka1) 35. Ka1 Qxc4 36. Rxa3 Re2 37. g6 1-0

