{[#] Black prepares the typical KID attack with Rg6, g5-g4, etc. In response,
White found a strong active defence :} 18. Kh1 $1 Rg6 19. Rg1 g4 $6 {Premature,
not expecting White's response.} (19... Bh6 20. g3 fxg3 21. Rxg3 Kh7 $13) 20.
g3 $1 {Usually we do not push the pawns on the flank where we are getting
attacked, but White is actually better mobilized than Black for the opening of
the kingside!} fxg3 21. Rxg3 Ndf6 22. Rg2 Nh7 23. Rag1 {[%csl Rg4]} Nef6 24.
Bh4 $1 {A strong idea, paralyzing black forces on the kingside.} Ng5 25. f4 (
25. Nf2 $1 $18 {would have completed White's excellent strategy as Nh3 would
be stopped and the g4-pawn would fall.}) 25... Nh3 26. f5 Rh6 27. Rf1 Ba6 28.
b5 Bb7 29. Rg3 Qf7 30. Bd1 Nh7 31. Rxh3 gxh3 32. Rg1 Kh8 33. Qd2 Rg8 34. Rg3
Bf8 35. Nf2 Rxg3 36. hxg3 Kg7 37. Nxh3 Be7 38. Ng5 Nxg5 39. Bxg5 Bxg5 40. Qxg5+
Kh7 41. Kh2 Qg7 42. Qxg7+ Kxg7 43. Kh3 Bc8 44. Kh4 Bd7 45. Kg5 Be8 46. Be2 Rh8
47. a4 Kh7 48. Nd1 Rg8+ 49. Kh4 Kh6 50. Nc3 Bf7 51. Bd1 Ra8 52. Be2 Be8 53. Bd1
a6 54. Be2 axb5 55. cxb5 Ra7 56. Bc4 Rg7 57. Be2 Rg8 58. Bd1 Kg7 59. Be2 Kf6
60. Bd1 Bf7 61. Be2 Ke7 62. Bd1 Kf6 63. Be2 Rf8 64. Bd1 Ra8 65. Be2 Be8 66. Bd1
Bd7 67. Be2 Rg8 68. Bd1 Bxf5 69. exf5 Kxf5 70. Bxh5 e4 71. g4+ Ke5 72. g5 Kd4
73. Ne2+ Ke3 74. g6 1-0

