{[#] In this game, Boris Gelfand used a similar defensive strategy as in the
previous one. In fact, this game is a precedent.} 23. fxg4 $1 ({Passive
defence like} 23. Kh1 Nh4 24. Rg1 Rg6 25. Be1 {would not be fruitful in the
view of} g3) 23... hxg4 24. g3 $1 {Blocking the kingside. A remarkable concept.
} fxg3 {Black goes all in, but to no avail.} (24... f3 25. Qf2 Qf8 26. Ne3 {
is clearly in White's favour as the kingside is blocked and he dominates on
the queenside.}) (24... Bh6 25. N1f2 $18) 25. Bg5 gxh2+ 26. Qxh2 Nf4 27. Nxf4
exf4 28. e5 $1 $40 {Suddenly, White attacks on the kingside and soon delivers
a mating attack.} dxe5 29. Qh4 Kf7 30. Rxf6+ Bxf6 31. Qh7+ Kf8 32. Bh6+ Ke8 33.
Qg6+ Ke7 34. Rxe5+ Bxe5 35. d6+ 1-0

